<P>UPON THE APPLICATION of MNP Ltd. (the &ldquo;Trustee&rdquo;), Trustee of the Estate of Cindy Hannele Chomistek, a bankrupt, for the advice and directions of this Honourable Court concerning entitlement to certain income tax refunds received by the Trustee as a result of disability tax credits claimed by the bankrupt on behalf of her disabled child following the date of her discharge from bankruptcy; AND UPON reading the written submissions of the Trustee, the bankrupt, the Court-appointed <EM>Amicus Curiae</EM>, and counsel for the Intervenor, the Alberta Association of Insolvency and Restructuring Professionals (&ldquo;AAIRP&rdquo;); AND UPON REVIEWING the proceedings had and taken herein to date; AND UPON this application being heard as a Special Application on May 11<SUP>th</SUP>, 2018; AND UPON being advised that the Office of the Superintendent of Bankruptcy was given notice of this application, but did not appear;</P>
<P>IT IS HEREBY ORDERED AND DIRECTED THAT:</P>
<P>1. The income tax refunds totalling $20,339.82 held by the Trustee, less the amount of $4,000.00 previously ordered to be paid to the <EM>Amicus Curiae</EM> as costs, shall be paid to the bankrupt, with the exception of the funds that were received from Canada Revenue Agency (&ldquo;CRA&rdquo;) on account of the calendar year 2013, which totalled $2,879.36, and any funds received from CRA on account of the bankrupt's earnings up to the date of her discharge on February 15<SUP>th</SUP>, 2014, which funds shall be retained by the Trustee for the benefit of the bankrupt estate.</P>
<P>2. Th e 2013 amount and any amount reflecting earnings up to the date of the bankrupt's discharge are to be treated by the Trustee as part of the bankrupt's &ldquo;income&rdquo;.</P>
<P>3. The Trustee and the <EM>Amicus Curiae</EM> shall have leave to apply to the Court in respect of any further claims for costs.</P>
<P>&ellip35; REGISTRAR</P>
