<BLOCK1><TI TOCID="I">AFFIDAVIT OF MARIE KOZLOWSKI SWORN ON DECEMBER 7, 2017</TI>
<P>Marie Kozlowski, of the City of Calgary, in the Province of Alberta, MAKE OATH AND SAY AS FOLLOWS:</P>
<P>1. I am a Chartered Insolvency and Restructuring Professional, a senior Vice President at Hardie &amp; Kelly Inc., Licensed Insolvency Trustee, and Treasurer of the Alberta Association of Insolvency and Restructuring Professionals (&ldquo;AAIRP&rdquo;). As such, I have persona] knowledge of the matters and facts hereinafter deposed to except where stated to be based upon information and belief, in which case I do verily believe the same to be true.</P>
<P>2. AAIRP represents Chartered Insolvency and Restructuring Professionals (CIRPs) and Licensed Insolvency Trustees (LITs) in bankruptcy in Alberta.</P>
<P>3. I am advised by Donna Carson, a member of AAIRP, and the Licensed Insolvency Trustee administering the bankruptcy of Cindy Hannele Chomistek, and do verily believe that:
<P1>(a) a Special Chambers Application has been scheduled on Friday, December 8, 2017 at 2:00 p.m. to deal with the treatment of disability tax credits, related to the Bankrupt's disabled child, claimed by the Bankrupt for pre-bankruptcy and bankruptcy tax years, but filed after the date of her discharge from bankruptcy;</P1>
<P1>(b) tax refunds arising from the Bankrupt's claims for disability tax returns were paid by Canada Revenue Agency to the Trustee in Bankruptcy, MNP Ltd., and are held in trust pending court order; and</P1>
<P1>(c) an <EM>amicus curiae</EM> was appointed by the Court in the within matter and has submitted a lengthy brief with respect to this issue.</P1></P>
<P>4. AAIRP would like to appear as intervenor in this matter, filing its own brief and making its own submissions because:
<P1>(a) its members will be affected by the decision facing the Court;</P1>
<P1>(b) it has special expertise and insight to bring to the issues facing the Court; and</P1>
<P1>(c) the Licensed Insolvency Trustee has no resources in the Estate to funds representation, so the interests of Licensed Insolvency Trustees, generally, would not be fully protected without the involvement of AAIRP as intervenor.</P1></P>
<P>5. I make this application in support of an adjournment of the Special Chambers Application and an order granting AAIRP intervenor status in the matter for the purposes of filing its own brief and making its own submissions on behalf of Chartered Insolvency and Restructuring Professionals and Licensed Insolvency Trustees in bankruptcy in Alberta and for no improper purpose.</P>
